Dataset Description

This dataset contains synthetic telemetry records used to simulate stability monitoring in enterprise AI deployments. The dataset was created to reproduce the stability evaluation experiments described in the AI-OS framework.

Each record represents a monitoring cycle and contains normalized system metrics used to compute the AI Deployment Stability Index (ADSI).

The dataset enables evaluation of:

• stability degradation detection
• anomaly detection using rolling statistics
• composite stability modeling across subsystems

⸻

Dataset Structure

Each telemetry record includes:

Field	Description
timestamp	Monitoring cycle timestamp
kpi_error	KPI misalignment error rate
retrieval_score	Retrieval system quality score
latency_deviation	Infrastructure latency variation
embedding_shift	Embedding drift magnitude

All values are normalized between 0 and 1.

⸻

Dataset Size
	•	500 simulated monitoring cycles
	•	3 degradation phases

1️⃣ Stable phase
2️⃣ Warning phase
3️⃣ Critical degradation phase

This progression enables controlled evaluation of stability tier transitions.

⸻

Dataset Purpose

The dataset is designed to:
	•	reproduce ADSI calculations
	•	validate stability tier classification
	•	simulate compound degradation scenarios
	•	demonstrate early failure detection compared to isolated metric monitoring

